12/06/2005
BRIJUNI, Croatia -- Foreign Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic and Slovenian counterpart Dimitrij Rupel signed a joint declaration Friday (10 June) on avoiding border incidents.
The signing took place during an inter-government meeting -- the first held at this level in 14 years.
Representatives of the two countries described the document as a building block in efforts to establish a political framework between Zagreb and Ljubljana.
The delegations also signed a readmission accord, as well as bilateral protocols on double taxation avoidance and co-operation in the customs sector, culture and education.
Croatian Prime Minister Ivo Sanader and Slovenian counterpart Janez Jansa said they have agreed to hold regular consultations to settle outstanding issues and improve bilateral ties.
(Vecernji list - 11/06/05;
HINA - 10/06/05)
